 advent of sound, to explore the challenges to convention that began in the 1960s and which continue into the twenty-first century. New digital technologies and the dominance of the moving image as an increasingly central part of everyday life have produced a radical rewriting of the rules of audio-visual address. It is not a technical treatise; instructive and accessible, this historically-based insight into filmmaking practice will prove invaluable to students of film and also appeal to a much wider readership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picturesxEditing. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh  aBreaking the Waves.  aRescued by Rover.  aThe Great Train Robbery.  aconventional editing forms.  acultural traditions.  afilm-editing technology.  afilmed fiction.  ahuman emotions.  asilent films.  aunbroken continuity.1 aFairservice, Don, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614138540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141385423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141385/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles